abla} \cdot \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) = 0 \] <p>Taking the Fourier transform:</p> \[\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{
abla} \cdot \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = 0 \] <p>Bringing the divergence operator outside the integral:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} \cdot \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = 0 \] <p>Simplifying the Fourier transform:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} \cdot 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},\omega) = 0 \]

\[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) = -  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} \] <p>Multiplying both sides by \(e^{-i \omega t}\):</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t}  = -   rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} \] <p>We can begin with the definition of the product rule:</p> \[  rac{d}{dt}(fg) = g  rac{f}{dt} + f rac{dg}{dt} \] <p>This can be rearranged to</p> \[ -f rac{dg}{dt} =  g  rac{df}{dt} -  rac{d}{dt}(fg) \] <p>We can take the \( rac{\partial \vec{B}}{\partial t}\) to be \(-f rac{dg}{dt}\) and fill in the rest of the rearranged product rule formula to get:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t}  = \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t} -  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t} \] <p>taking the derivative in the first term on the right side gives us:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t}  =-i \omega \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} -  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t} \] <p>Then we can integrate both sides of the equation:</p> \[ \int_{-infty}^{infty} \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t}  = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} -i \omega \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} -  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t}dt \] <p>Bringing the curl outside the integral:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} -i \omega \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} -  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t}dt \] <p>Simplifying the Fourier transform on the left side:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} -i \omega \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} -  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t}dt\] <p>Now the on the right hand side we can change the sum in the integral to a sum of integrals and simplify the fourier transform. </p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = i \omega \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}}{\partial t}dt\] <p>Then the time derivative is linear so we bring it out of the last remaining integral term</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = i \omega \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} -  rac{\partial}{\partial t}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-i \omega t} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)dt\] <p>Then we can simplify the FT.</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = -i \omega 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},
u)  -   rac{\partial  	ilde{B}(\vec{r},
u)}{\partial t}dt\] <p>We can recognize that this last term is a time derivative of a function in frequency space so that derivative will be 0 resulting in:</p> \[\vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = - i \omega 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},\omega)\]

\[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) = \vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) +  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} \] <p>Using a similar technique as above, we can first multiply on both sides by \(e^{-i \omega t}\) and then take the partial deriavte on the right hand side and expand it with the product rule:</p> \[ \ e^{-i \omega t} \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) = e^{-i \omega t}\vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) + e^{i \omega t}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} \] <p>then we make the substitution:</p> \[ e^{-i \omega t}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} =  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} - \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t} \] \[ \ e^{-i \omega t} \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) = e^{-i \omega t}\vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) +  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} - \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t} \] <p>Then we can integrate both sides:</p> \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-i \omega t} \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) dt = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-i \omega t}\vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t}dt \] <p>On the left we can bring the curl operator outside of the time integral and on the right we can simplify the \(\vec{J}\) FT.</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-i \omega t}  \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) dt = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t}dt \] <p>Then we can simplify the FT on the left hand side:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}}{\partial t}dt \] <p>We can take the derivative in the last term to get </p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} -i \omega \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)  e^{-i \omega t}dt \] <p>which then becomes:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt  + i \omega \vec{D}(	ilde{r},
u) \] <p>Then the time derivative is linear so we bring it out of the last remaining integral term</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + rac{\partial}{\partial t} \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-i \omega t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},t) dt  + i \omega \vec{D}(	ilde{r},
u) \] <p>Finally we can simplify the last FT:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) + rac{\partial}{\partial t}\vec{D}(\vec{r},
u)  + i \omega 	ilde{D}(\vec{r},
u) \] <p>This is another time derivative of a frequency function so it goes to 0 leaving the final result </p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},
u)= 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},
u) ++ i \omega 	ilde{D}(\vec{r},
